Cuno: Variable["whirling.kimnotes_entered_wo_kim"]
Conceptualization: He went with the 'Furies'. Perhaps the internal strife it implies was not so off after all? Or perhaps to honour your wishes? Or for some other reason. Hard to say...
Jump to: [paperwork!]

Cuno: The boy picks up the notes and shuffles through some of the case names: "'The Child', 'Dom's Unfinished', 'Dom's Unfinished 2', 'The Man With the Hole in His Head'... Boring ass shit," he concludes.
Cuno: "Oh... 'Motorcycle Emptiness' -- that's a cool case. Cuno can solve that shit for the bino."
You: "Yeah, Kim is such a binoclard."
Cuno: "Pig..." he says with a frown. "It's cool for Cuno to rip on the 'clard, but he took a bullet for you. You gonna shitmouth Cuno too if he falls in battle?"
Kim Kitsuragi: "I had Garte open the door to your room." He closes the notes. "You were running a low bacterial fever the first night."
You: "Thank you for keeping this... thing alive a little longer." (Point to yourself.)
You: "I saw... apocalyptic visions. Of the darkness... behind darkness... *behind* darkness..."
You: "I'm such a burden. I should just fuck off..."
You: "I thought I was dead for a moment."
paperwork!
Half-Finished Paperwork: These are fragments of the lieutenant's paperwork, left unfinished. Notes on this and other recent cases.
Esprit de Corps: "To inquire about the Lieutenant-Yefreitor, sir. I am his partner," says Satellite-Officer Jean Vicquemare, standing in the doorway.

Esprit de Corps: "Then why are you wasting time here?" coughs Kim. "He's out there. In Martinaise. Unsupervised, *without cover*. You need to get there..." His cough gets the best of him, he grabs a glass.
You: "It just good-humoured banter among friends."
You: "You're right, I shouldn't call him that."
You: "I call it like I see it, Cuno."

Esprit de Corps: Twenty-eight kilometres to the northeast, in the infirmary of Precinct 57, Lieutenant Kim 'Pinball' Kitsuragi rests under a heart monitor. A triage sign coloured yellow hangs from his injury record -- safe, it means. He coughs, propped up against the pillow.
Esprit de Corps: "Why are you here?" asks the man as the cough fit resides. His eyes are black and moist.
Cuno: The boy hesitates for a moment, then nods. "No one tells Cuno what to call something, but the bino was alright in Cuno's book." He taps his chest solemnly. "Cuno's pig."

You: "Look, Cuno, Lieutenant Kitsuragi's notes."
Cuno: "For you, maybe," he replies seriously. "But take it from the Cunn: Binos don't always get that. They get their feelings hurt. Cuno doesn't want this for your pal. He's alright in Cuno's book."
Empathy: He's right, you know? The lieutenant probably doesn't enjoy being called a binoclard -- the four-eyed dork.
